{"name":"Lasgun","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Lasguns are the basic weapon of Imperial Guard troopers, and as such are the most common las weapon in existence. They come in many varieties and patterns, and the continued survival of the Imperium owes much to their reliability, simplicity of design, and ease of use.</p>","availability":"common","weight":4,"class":"basic","type":"","range":100,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":3,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+3","damageType":"energy","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":60,"value":60},"reload":"Full","special":"Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Range/lasgun.svg","effects":[],"_id":"KvQnF9fRniKquByi"}
{"name":"Laspistol","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Compact and reliable, laspistols are a favourite weapon for Imperial officers and gang leaders alike.</p>","availability":"common","weight":1.5,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":2,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+2","damageType":"energy","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":30,"value":30},"reload":"Half","special":"Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Range/laspistol.svg","effects":[],"_id":"N4LsynXPUvICmQvi"}
{"name":"Hot-shot Laspistol","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Specialised variants of the&nbsp;standard las weapon design, hotshot&nbsp;weapons use stronger power&nbsp;packs that provide extra energy for each shot.&nbsp;High ranking military officers and elite forces&nbsp;such as the Militarum Tempestus use them frequently, but other&nbsp;Imperial agencies with sufficient means also favour the extra&nbsp;stopping power they provide against heretics and other threats.&nbsp;Hot-shot weapons use a 10 kg backpack power source rather&nbsp;than a standard plug-in pack, even for the smaller hot-shot pistol.&nbsp;Larger packs mean greater power behind each shot, but make&nbsp;reloading more impractical, which is a trade-off most are willing&nbsp;to make. Hot-shot weapons can also be linked to larger backpacks&nbsp;for additional ammunition (see page 162). Hot-shot weapons do&nbsp;not benefit from the Las Weapon Variable Setting rules.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":4,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":20,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":2,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"energy","penetration":"7","clip":{"max":40,"value":40},"reload":"2 Full","special":"","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Range/laspistol.svg","effects":[],"_id":"SoVflxMBq4dq81Ud"}
{"name":"Hot-shot Lasgun","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Specialised variants of the standard las weapon design, hotshot weapons use stronger power packs that provide extra energy for each shot. High ranking military officers and elite forces such as the Militarum Tempestus use them frequently, but other Imperial agencies with sufficient means also favour the extra stopping power they provide against heretics and other threats. Hot-shot weapons use a 10 kg backpack power source rather than a standard plug-in pack, even for the smaller hot-shot pistol. Larger packs mean greater power behind each shot, but make reloading more impractical, which is a trade-off most are willing to make. Hot-shot weapons can also be linked to larger backpacks for additional ammunition (see page 162). Hot-shot weapons do not benefit from the Las Weapon Variable Setting rules.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":6,"class":"basic","type":"","range":60,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":3,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"energy","penetration":"7","clip":{"max":30,"value":30},"reload":"2 Full","special":"","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Range/lasgun.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YSmbYGMlg0qd0evV"}
{"name":"Digi-Weapon","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Impossibly advanced, the digi-weapons of the enigmatic Jokaero slip easily onto a user&rsquo;s fingers like rings and fire either with a simple press of a button or by squeezing the band. The weapons themselves vary immensely and never seem to completely run out of ammunition, a facet of their design that remains a mystery to the Adeptus Mechanicus.</p>\n<p>Table 2&ndash;1: Armoury Imperialis on page 44 lists the most common digi-weapon, which incorporates the profile of a laspistol. Other digi-weapon types can include ones incorporating the profile of a flamer, grav pistol, inferno pistol, needle pistol, plasma pistol, or others at the GM&rsquo;s discretion, by using that weapon&rsquo;s damage, penetration, and weapon qualities. The rate of fire, range, and clip size are always set to the values listed in Table 2&ndash;1: Armoury Imperialis (see page 44), no matter the weapon&rsquo;s normal values. Digi-weapons are worn as rings and do not prevent the hand from performing other tasks. They take one hour to recharge between shots, cannot be modified, and always have an Availability of Near Unique.</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":0.5,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":3,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+2","damageType":"energy","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"","special":"Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Range/laser-blast.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YqyTF2k5EdVNqPSN"}
{"name":"Laslock","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>On worlds where the standard power pack pattern has been lost, laslocks are commonly used in place of lasguns. Often found in the hands of desperate and poorly equipped insurgents or renegades, laslocks might be scratch-built or modifications of antique or damaged las rifles brought back into service by scav-workshops and heretek forges. A laslock&rsquo;s jury-rigged cells are temperamental things at best, but still potent, firing a more powerful discharge than that of a standard lasgun. Laslocks do not benefit from the Las Weapon Variable Setting rules.</p>","availability":"plentiful","weight":4,"class":"basic","type":"","range":70,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"energy","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"Half","special":"Unreliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Range/laslock.svg","effects":[],"_id":"iV8zbZ8gAu9UwZgP"}
{"name":"Long Las","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The long las is a specialised version of the basic lasgun designed for snipers. The longer barrel and precise collimator allows for accurate shots at much farther ranges, with little of the signature loud crack of other las weapons. The barrel length and lack of a rapid-firing mode, however, make it impractical for close range operations.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"scarce","weight":4.5,"class":"basic","type":"","range":150,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+3","damageType":"energy","penetration":"1","clip":{"max":40,"value":40},"reload":"Full","special":"Accurate, Felling (4), Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Range/longlas.svg","effects":[],"_id":"qpB3GGmgcUzF4hGV"}
